  "prompt": "What's a good moveset for Lycanroc in Pokemon Sun and Moon?",
  "response": "Lycanroc is a versatile Rock-type Pok\u00e9mon that can be trained to be an effective attacker in Pok\u00e9mon Sun and Moon. Here are some movesets depending on the Lycanroc form:\n\n**Lycanroc (Midday Form):**\n1. **Stone Edge** - High power Rock-type move with critical-hit potential.\n2. **Drill Run** - Ground-type move that hits critical more often and can cover Rock-type weaknesses.\n3. **Accelerock** - Priority move that hits first most of the time, useful for taking out weakened foes.\n4. **Swords Dance** - Boosts Lycanroc's attack power by two stages, making it a powerful sweeper.\n\n**Lycanroc (Midnight Form):**\n1. **Stone Edge** - High power Rock-type move with critical-hit potential.\n2. **Fire Fang** - Can cover Lycanroc\u2019s weaknesses to Grass-types and hit Steel-types effectively.\n3. **Crunch** - Strong Dark-type move that can lower the opponent\u2019s Defense, useful for a reliable coverage.\n4. **Swords Dance** - Again, boosts attack power significantly, allowing Lycanroc to break through defenses.\n\n**Lycanroc (Dusk Form):**\n1. **Stone Edge** - Again, a high-power, crit-heavy Rock move.\n2. **Accelerock** - Priority move, which provides quick takedowns on weakened opponents.\n3. **Fire Fang/Thunder Fang** - Coverage option. Fire Fang for Grass and Steel types, Thunder Fang for Water and Flying types.\n4. **Swords Dance** - Boosting Lycanroc's attack consistently makes it a strong threat.\n\nFor all forms, consider using items like:\n- **Life Orb** for boosted damage at the cost of HP.\n- **Focus Sash** to ensure Lycanroc can survive one hit and set up Swords Dance.\n- **Rockium Z** for devastating Continental Crush moves based on its Rock-type attacks.\n\nThese moves should enable Lycanroc to handle various threats and perform well in battles.",
